t: Bow*p down thine ear, O Lord,*s hear me: for I am poor and needy.
Preserve*p my soul; for I am holy: O thou my God, save thy servant that trusteth in thee.
Be*p merciful unto me, O Lord: for I cry unto thee daily.
Rejoice*p the soul of thy servant: for unto thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.
For*p thou, Lord, art good, and ready to forgive; and plenteous in mercy unto all them that call upon thee.
Give*p ear, O Lord,*s unto my prayer; and attend to the voice of my supplications.
In*p the day of my trouble I will call upon thee: for thou wilt answer me.
Among*p the gods there is none like unto thee, O Lord; neither are there any works like unto thy works.
All*p nations whom thou hast made shall come and worship before thee, O Lord; and shall glorify thy name.
For*p thou art great, and doest wondrous things: thou art God alone.
Teach*p me thy way, O Lord;*s I will walk in thy truth: unite my heart to fear thy name.
I*p will praise thee, O Lord my God, with all my heart: and I will glorify thy name for evermore.
For*p great is thy mercy toward me: and thou hast delivered my soul from the lowest hell.
O*p God, the proud are risen against me, and the assemblies of violent men have sought after my soul; and have not set thee before them.
But*p thou, O Lord, art a God full of compassion, and gracious, longsuffering, and plenteous in mercy and truth.
O*p turn unto me, and have mercy upon me; give thy strength unto thy servant, and save the son of thine handmaid.
Shew*p me a token for good; that they which hate me may see it, and be ashamed: because thou, Lord,*s hast holpen me, and comforted me.
